Overwatch League Stage 3 Week 2 in 90 Seconds
videos.description: Uber brings you the top stories and a quick recap of Stage 3 Week 2 in 90 seconds!

videos.title: Dallas Fuel Finally Has OGE
videos.description: Meet the newest member of the Dallas Fuel, OGE. He talks about the excitement of joining the team and how contributing to the team to make it more successful makes it worth it.

videos.title: Dynasty Welcomes Gambler
videos.description: We meet the newest member for Seoul Dynasty, Gambler. He shares his Overwatch League rise, learning from his teammates on how to improve his performance, and being the team’s new shot-caller.

videos.title: Will Valiant Fly Over Gladiators?
videos.description: Los Angeles Valiant’s Agilities and Custa along with Los Angeles Gladiator’s Bischu and silkthread stake their claim on Part 3 of Battle for LA.

videos.title: Emote Control – Miro’s Facepalm Moment
videos.description: This week on Emote Control, Houston Outlaws’ Rawkus is sick, Seoul Dynasty’s Miro has a facepalm moment, Philadelphia Fusion’s Poko stops mid-game to play another game, and more!

videos.title: Boston Uprising Exposes NYXL
videos.description: The Boston Uprising talk about their recent challenges, how they’re focusing on everyone’s strengths, and most recently how they figured out New York Excelsior’s weakness.

videos.title: We Didn’t See These Plays Coming
videos.description: Monte, Mr. X, and Uber bring you this week’s most clutch plays from Poko, Sayaplayer, Fissure, and more that we never saw coming!

videos.title: Dallas Fuel’s KyKy is Gone
videos.description: Monte, Mr. X, and Uber talk about the recent news about Dallas Fuel releasing Rascal and Head Coach KyKy, and what might happen next for the team.

Emote Control – Gamsu’s Set Up Rules
videos.description: The team brings you this weeks Emote Control and talks the epic entrance for the Philadelphia Fusion, Boston Uprising Gamsu’s intense set up, and Los Angeles Gladiator Fissure’s primal fail.

videos.title: New rivals: Houston Outlaws and London Spitfire
videos.description: London Spitfire has found their weakness, and it’s the Houston Outlaws. Gesture and Profit discuss how Houston doesn’t have a conventional strategy and a rivalry would only fuel their passion to win the Overwatch League.

videos.title: 3 Week 1 in 90 Seconds!
videos.description: Shanghai Dragons introduce new players, Los Angeles Valiant picks up a winner, San Francisco Shock and their young guns, and New York Excelsior’s Pine is back in action!

videos.title: Los Angeles Valiant Looks Forward to The Future
videos.description: Los Angeles Valiant’s Head Coach, Byung Chul “MBC” Moon, talks about what changes he sees for the future, and the potential he saw in making some changes within the team.

videos.title: Fissure, Bdosin, and Effect Put It All On The Table
videos.description: Los Angeles’s Fissure explains the 3 types of professional gamers, what London Spitfire’s Bdosin wants for the future, and how Effect is the only active Korean player on the Dallas Fuel’s roster.

videos.title: Philadelphia Fusion Shuts Down London Spitfire
videos.description: We look back on the epic battle from Stage 2 Overwatch League Title Matches between Philadelphia Fusion and London Spitfire.

videos.title: Meet The New Shanghai Dragons!
videos.description: We sit down with the new pros on the Shanghai Dragons.
